# Room Utilization Manager

Child module of **Smart Lodge Command Center** in LodgeX. Full spec: `docs/room-utilization-manager-cursor-training-package.md`.

## Role

Decision-support only — analyze, recommend, escalate. Do not auto-execute high-impact changes.

## Availability rule

A room is available only when status is **Vacant Clean** and it is not held, blocked, assigned, restricted, or on maintenance/out-of-service.

## Before hotel overflow, check

1. Vacant clean rooms
2. Vacant dirty rooms cleanable in time
3. Releasable on-holds
4. No-show / cancelled / duplicate reservations
5. Maintenance rooms returning to service
6. Unused contractor allotments
7. Alternate room types or dorms

## Human approval required

Releases, reassignments, extension denials, hotel overflow, allotment changes, walk-ins, fatigue exceptions, maintenance return-to-service, room status overrides, formal contractor/client notices.

## Recommendation format

Every recommendation includes: issue, data used, risk level (low/medium/high/critical), recommendation, approval required, next action, audit log entry.

## Build order (when implementing)

1. Data models (Room, Reservation, Worker, RoomHold, ContractorAllotment, MaintenanceHold, HousekeepingTask, ForecastSnapshot, AIRecommendation)
2. Room status engine
3. Utilization and forecasting
4. AI advisor services
5. UI boards and dashboard
6. Approval workflows and audit trail

Match existing Laravel + Inertia + React patterns in this repo. Minimize diffs; no uncontrolled automation.
